## 3. How the existing apps should be woven in

### SKNore
Becomes the universal policy engine called by all apps before AI, export, publish, deploy, and release.

### SovereignVariables
Becomes the secure config authoring and exchange surface. It should feed vault-controlled secret release, not just local exports.

### SovereignPrimitives
Becomes the blueprint/reference implementation for zones, capsules, guardrails, seals, and decision ledger logic.

### SkyeVault / SkyeVault Pro
Become the operational vault and storage substrate for secure state, approvals, break-glass, and cross-app import/export.

### SkyDex 4.6 / SuperIDE shell
Remain the orchestration bench and launcher, but move from browser-only handoffs to signed sovereign interaction contracts.

### SkyeHawk
Becomes the shared sovereign navigation surface. It should stop living as a one-off launcher pattern inside individual platforms and instead become the hidden-command and visible-menu layer that can open SkyeCDE, platform systems, recovery lanes, and role-approved app clusters across the whole 0s.

### SkyeDocxPro / SkyeBlog
Become content producers that output classified, sealed, and route-aware sovereign packages.

### SkyeChat / SkyeMail
Become policy-aware communication endpoints for sovereign distribution, not just plain output destinations.

### 0megaSkyeGate
Becomes the mandatory AI execution gateway and provider boundary for the whole 0s.

